    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You're hunch was completely right: see this jsfiddle:\nhttp://jsfiddle.net/S6uDj/1/\n\nJust wrapping an `<h1>` in a `<div>` pair messes up the subsection numbering:\nthe following HTML gives the same result as the one I posted from the IPython Notebook:\n\n```\n<div> <h1> First </h1> </div>\n\n<h2> Second </h2>\n<h2> Third </h2>\n\n<h1> Fourth </h1>\n```\n\nSo what can we do about this...? (I hope the answer is not: write a custom JS extension... But that would certainly be a fun (?) challenge!)\n"
