    "body": "Here is some JQuery code that (apparently) numbers chapters (`h1`) and sections (`h2`):\n\n```\n$(document).ready(function(){\n    $(\"h1\").each(function(index1) {\n\n        $(this).prepend(\"Chapter \" + (index1+1) + \". \");\n\n        $(\"h2\").each(function(index2) {\n            $(this).prepend((index1+1) + \".\" + (index2+1) + \". \");\n     });\n   });\n});\n```\n\nOf course, this is no good if there are already numbers, but checking that requires more JavaScript than I currently know (next step).\n\nHow can this kind of thing then be registered to run automatically? I guess whenever a new heading cell is created?\n(Though actually only cells _below_ the just-created heading cell need to have their numbers updated.)\n"
  },
